<HEADLINE> Premier Calls for Setting up First-Rate Book Distribution System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Xinhua Bookstore Chain should
be built into a first-rate national book distribution system to
help improve the quality of the Chinese nation and promote
socialist ethical and cultural progress, Premier Li Peng said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The premier made the call when meeting with representatives
from the bookstore's national chain at its 60th anniversary
celebration.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist
Party and the State Council, Li congratulated and thanked all
those working in the chain as well as the representatives for
their contributions to China's development since its establishment
in a cave dwelling in the revolutionary base in Yan'an six decades
ago.
</P>
<P>
"Publication and distribution of books is a significant part of
the promotion of ethical and cultural progress in the country,
which is as important as economic development," the premier
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He urged Xinhua bookstores across the country to further
improve service quality in a time when China is building a
socialist market economy, and make greater contributions to the
cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The bookstore chain has grown into a national distribution
network of book and audio-video products, with more than 2,800
stores and 10,000-plus retail outlets, and has more than 100,000
employees.
</P>
<P>
At present, the chain is responsible for 90 percent of all the
books sold in China, and 80 percent of the total sales of the
books.
</P>
<P>
State leaders Li Tieying, Luo Gan and Hong Xuezhi also attended
the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
