<HEADLINE> China's Xia Advances to Semis in Langkawi Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China's top tennis player
Xia Jiaping beat Belgium's Timothy Aerts 6-2, 6-2 on Thursday to
sail into last four of the Malaysia Langkawi circuit tennis
championship.
</P>
<P>
Xia, a key Davis Cup player, will meet South Korea's Yoon
Yong-il, a 6-3, 6-2 winner over Filippo Veglio of Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Mark Petchey of Britain is to meet Nicolas Thomann of France in
the other semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Petchey defeated American Charlie Singer 6-1, 7-5, and Thomann
defeated Kotaro Miyachi of Japan 6-4, 6-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
