<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kohl to Visit Asia-Pacific Region to Boost Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl is
scheduled to begin an 11-day tour next week to Brunei, Australia,
New Zealand and Hong Kong in a bid to further promote Germany's
business interests in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
As the Bonn government said, Kohl, accompanied by more than 12
leading German businessmen, is expected to arrive first in Brunei
on April 30.
</P>
<P>
Kohl's trip followed a series of visits to the region by German
ministers, including Economics Minister Guenter Rexrodt.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, Kohl has visited the fast-growing economies in Asia
at least once a year as part of his efforts to boost Germany's
business interests in the region.
</P>
<P>
German Economics Ministry data showed that Asia has become
Germany's second most important trading partner after Europe,
accounting for 12.8 percent of German trade.  
</P>
</TEXT>
