<HEADLINE> Kostov Nominated Bulgarian Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Ivan Kostov, leader of the United
Democratic Forces (UDF), was officially nominated Bulgaria's prime
minister by his party today.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian President Petar Stoyanov announced immediately that
Kostov would be the next head of government after the UDF alliance
won the April 19 parliamentary election.
</P>
<P>
Under the constitution, the president will charge Kostov with
forming a government, which must then be approved by parliament.
</P>
<P>
The (UDF) alliance is expected to have 136 or 137 of the
240-seat parliament.
</P>
<P>
Kostov, 47, an economist and mathematician by training, was
finance minister in the coalition government of Dimitar Popov in
1991 and the Union of Democratic Forces minority government of
1992. He was elected head of the Union of Democratic Forces in
December 1994.
</P>
<P>
At the UDF meeting, Yordan Sokolov was chosen as chairman of
parliament. 
</P>
