<HEADLINE> Mozambican Govt Satisfied with Solution for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican government has
been satisfied with the solution of the hostage problem in Peru.
</P>
<P>
Mozambican Foreian Affairs Minister Leonardo Simao said here
today that the Peruvian government is gratified with the news
that the incident has come to an end.
</P>
<P>
The Peruvian government had been patient in searching for a
solution to the problem, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that diplomatic missions should be respected.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that a combined force of Peruvian soldiers
and policemen launched an attack Tuesday on the gunmen who
held 71 people as hostages at the Japanese Embassay in Peru for
more than four months.
</P>
<P>
During the attack, 14 gunmen were killed, 70 hostages saved
and one died. enditem

