<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Meets Kazakh President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin told
Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev here today that there is no
obstacle to furthering the friendly relations between China and
Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
"We want to join efforts with Kazakhstan in building a 21st
century oriented partnership of all-round cooperation" between the
countries, said the Chinese president, who is here for a five-day
visit to Russia.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Nazarbayev met before signing a five nation accord
here with the presidents of Russia, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan on
reducing arms in border areas.
</P>
<P>
Jiang praised Nazarbayev for his contributions to the
Sino-Kazakh relations. He said China highly appreciates efforts by
Nazarbayev to develop good-neighborly relations, friendship and
mutually beneficial cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev, on his part, expressed his belief that there is no
problem between the two countries and they should increase
cooperation in economy and trade.
</P>
<P>
Noting that his country have had effective discussions with
China about cooperation on railway, transportation and in oil
industry, the Kazakh president expressed his hope to speed up the
cooperation process.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome the investment and cooperation of Chinese
enterprises in Kazakhstan," Nazarbayev said, adding that Chinese
enterprises have a competitive edge in his country.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh president pointed out that his country stands
against national splittism and activities by any organization aimed
at dividing China by using Kazakh territories.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciation for Nazarbayev's policy
statement, and his hope that Kazakhstan will take actions in this
aspect to stop anti-Chinese splittism activities and secure the
social stability and economic development of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also hoped that the departments concerned from the Kazakh
and Chinese governments will increase cooperation in this area and
take strong measures against international terrorism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
