<HEADLINE> Mozambican Ruling Party to Hold National Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Mozambican ruling Frelimo
party will hold its Seventh National Congress in Matola City near
here on May 19-24, the Mozambique Information
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Participants of the congress will discuss some important
issues which will make impact on the party's activities in the
years to come, Mariano Matsinha, a member of the Political
Commission of the party's Central Committee, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
These included the issues related to the party's life, social
and economic problems, and international relations among others.
</P>
<P>
Established on June 25, 1962, the Frelimo party now has 1.1
million members. enditem
