<HEADLINE> Indo-Pak Can Collaborate Despite Differences: Gujral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 24 (Xinhua) -- India has told Pakistan that
despite some differences it was confident that both sides could
"collaborate effectively" for mutual benefits, Press Trust of
India (PTI) said here this evening.
</P>
<P>
In his reply to Pakistan Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif's greeting
message on his appointment as India's new prime minister, Gujral
said, "Though we may not agree on all issues, we see a wide range
of subjects on which we believe we can collaborate effectively."
</P>
<P>
"We are glad that after a long break, our two countries have
recently revived the process of dialogue on all outstanding
issues. With each of us showing a constructive and forward looking
approach, we are confident that our exchanges will be useful and
lead to mutually beneficial results," he said in the message.
</P>
<P>
The Indian prime minister further said that he looked forward
to meeting Sharif in Male during the summit meeting of the South
Asian Association for Regional Cooperation to renew personal
contact which they had established in Islamabad some years ago.
</P>
<P>
In a congratulation message to Gujral on his appointment as
India's new prime minister, the Pakistani prime minister said that
Gujral's selection had raised hopes of improving bilateral ties
between the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
