<HEADLINE> Germany to Provide Aid to Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The German government has budgeted 41
million US dollars for development and technical aid in Zimbabwe in
its 1996/97 financial year.
</P>
<P>
German Ambassador Norwin Graf Leutrum today said the money was
mainly to fund projects in the agricultural, health and environmental
sectors.
</P>
<P>
He said German development aid in the world had decreased because
of serious budget problems it now faces after the reunification
of the country.
</P>
<P>
''Part of the funding is now directed at re-building the former
eastern part of the country,'' he said, adding that once this was
through more aid to developing countries would follow. enditem

