<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Kyrgyz Presidents Vow to Strengthen Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China is always willing to be "a
good friend, good neighbor and good partner" of Kyrgyzstan,
Chinese President Jiang Zemin said in talks with his Kyrgyz
counterpart Askar Akayev in Moscow today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang appreciated Kyrgyzstan's understanding and support for
China's position on some key issues including Taiwan, Tibet and
fighting against ethnic splittism, saying that the two neighbors
should strengthen cooperation on combating ethnic splittism.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the two countries have more and more in common,
and the long-term, stable development of friendly Sino-Kyrgyz
relations is both the strong desire of the two peoples and the
noble mission of the two countries' leaders.
</P>
<P>
Recalling Jiang's visit to Kyrgyzstan last year, Akayev said
the visit, a very successful one, has deeply impressed the Kyrgyz
people and forcefully enhanced the mutually beneficial cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Noting that China has become a major trade partner of his
country, Akayev expressed satisfaction with the development of the
relations between China and Kyrgyzstan.
</P>
<P>
Regarding opposing splittism as a responsibility of the
international community, Akayev said that Kyrgyzstan unreservedly
denounces splittism and will take various measures to stop any
splittist activities against China in the country while increasing
cooperation with China in this field.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents met before signing an agreement on the
reduction of military forces along border areas between China,
Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
Jiang hailed the agreement, which followed another agreement
signed a year ago on confidence building in the military field in
border areas of the five countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the two documents, together with an agreement on border
areas between China and Kyrgyzstan, will not only be conducive to
consolidating and expanding the good-neighborly and friendly ties
but also be helpful to promoting prosperity and stability in
border areas between them.
</P>
<P>
They also set up a good model for establishing mutual trust
between nations, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Akayev agreed, saying the signing of the agreements filled the
whole Eurasian continent with a peaceful and friendly atmosphere.
</P>
</TEXT>
