<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Students Clash with Riot Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- University of Zimbabwe students today
clashed with riot police as they embarked on a class boycott to press
their demands for payment of loans to all students.
</P>
<P>
The clashes left a trail of destruction. Rubble and litter
were strewn all over the campus, while roads were closed with
barricades made of rubbish bins, uprooted road signs and tree
branches.
</P>
<P>
Business at the institution had closed by nine a.m. as people
including the administrative staff fled from police teargas which
engulfed the whole campus.
</P>
<P>
A few students, however, still milled around the campus which
appeared to be calm by mid-afternoon.
</P>
<P>
President of the Students Representative Council Learnmore Majongwe
told the Zimbabwe News Agency that students were riled by the
Ministry of Higher Education which had failed to meet their ultimatum
of a response to the students' demands within three days.
</P>
<P>
''We feel all students who applied for sponsorships must get money
because they are in need, but the ministry is insisting on vetting
them,'' said Majongwe.
</P>
<P>
The university has in the past been a scene of violence because of
the frequent running battles between students and the police. enditem

