<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Sees Rising Prices of Staples </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Prices of foodstuffs continued to
maintain an upward trend in Nigeria in the first quarter of this year
despite the deceleration of the overall inflation rate.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures from the Federal Office of Statistics (FOS) show
that the composite consumer price index stood at 2723.4 in February,
one percent up from 2697.7 recorded in January.
</P>
<P>
The January figure itself was a 1.1 percent rise from the 2668.8 in
December last year.
</P>
<P>
In the three-month period from December 1996 to February 1997,
according to FOS, the rise in the index was caused by upward movement
in the prices of food items, while prices of clothing, footwear,
household appliances and personal items fell slightly in most places.
</P>
<P>
Inflation rate for February decelerated to 24.4 percent from 26.7
percent in January, a marked difference from the 28 percent in
December 1996 and 72 percent in December 1995.
</P>
<P>
Despite the declining inflation rate, the increase in prices of
essentials reveals a dangerous trend in the country's economic life,
according to a FOS news bulletin.
</P>
<P>
Items such as footwear, household appliances and even clothing can
be avoided by the poor class, while staples such as beans, yam and
plantains are essentials to the poor.
</P>
<P>
The result is that disposable income of the class continues to
diminish while the price decline in household appliances favors those
who can afford it, FOS said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970425.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Tajik Presidents Praise Five-Nation Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Making the comment when meeting with Rakhmonov, Jiang said that
today marks an important date in the development of relations
between China and neighboring Tajikistan, Russia, Kazakhstan and
Kyrgyzstan.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov said that the accord will not only help promote the
development of friendly relations between the two countries, but
also contribute to peace and security in the Asian-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said China attaches great importance to the bilateral
relations and both leaders shared the view that top-level contacts
contribute much to this friendly relationship.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said Tajikistan's decision to set up an embassy in
Beijing will further strengthen ties between the two neighbors.
</P>
<P>
With the establishment of the embassy in Beijing, the two
nations will have better cooperation in various fields, Rakhmonov
agreed.
</P>
<P>
He added that the concerted efforts by both sides have resulted
in improved transportation conditions which will surely facilitate
cooperation in their economy and trade.
</P>
<P>
On Rakhmonov's remarks about negotiations between the Tajik
government and the opposition, Jiang said China hopes that
national reconciliation can be achieved and national rejuvenation
attained in Tajikistan as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said he is confident that the situation in Tajikistan and
central Asia will surely improve. 
</P>
