<HEADLINE> Jiang's Visit to Russia A Success: Chinese FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China's Vice Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen today hailed Chinese President Jiang Zemin's
ongoing Russia tour as "a success."
</P>
<P>
Qian told a press conference here this afternoon that Jiang and
his Russian counterpart Boris Yeltsin discussed Wednesday the
bilateral political, military and economic relations as well as
major international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The meeting between the heads of states was the fourth official
meeting between the two, Qian noted.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the two sides pledged to further promote
non-governmental exchanges and cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister stressed that the agreement on reduction
of military forces in border areas between China and Russia,
Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan and Tajikistan signed today by President
Jiang and the other four presidents "is of great significance for
the peace and stability of the region."
</P>
<P>
He reiterated that it is necessary for both China and Russia to
establish normal state-to-state relations, which will be most
beneficial to the two neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that the current partnership between China and Russia
is neither a kind of alliance nor directed at any third party.
Instead, it will conduce to peace and stability of not only the
region but also the world at large, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian is currently accompanying Jiang on a five-day visit to
Russia, which is scheduled to end on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
