<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-24 17:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Civilians Wounded by Israeli Forces in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Israeli forces today wounded a
policeman and two civilians in south Lebanon as Israeli
helicopters swept the area and opened machinegun fire.
</P>
<P>
Security sources in south Lebanon said that around 2:15
p.m. (1115 GMT) two Israeli military helicopters launched a sweep
near the crossing point of kfar Tibnit in the central sector of
south Lebanon and hit a car running toward the Israeli self-
proclaimed "security zone."
</P>
<P>
Abdullah Masoul, a sergeant of the Interior Security Force, who
was driving the dark blue Mercedez, and Daoud Idrikh, who was
sitting beside Masoul, were injured, the anonymous sources said.
</P>
<P>
The tow men have been moved by an ambulance to a hospital in
Marjaroun inside the Israeli-occupied border strip.
</P>
<P>
Hassan Ismail Doughman, 17, was also wounded by machinegun fire
opened by Israeli forces at the town of kfar Tibnit from a nearby
position, according to the same sources.
</P>
<P>
The incidents took place less than 24 hours after a five-nation
committee supervising the implementation of a cease-fire in the
border area held a meeting in the south Lebanese border town of
Naqoura to discuss a complaint filed by Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israel claimed that a roadside bomb which the Lebanese
guerrillas detonated, killed tow members of the Israeli-backed
South Lebanon army militia and wounded one at Tair Harfa on April
14.
</P>
<P>
It added in the complaint that the three militiamen were on
vacation in a civilian vehicle when they were attacked by the
guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
However, during the Wednesday meeting in the headquarters of
the U.N. peace-keeping force in south Lebanon, the Lebanese
delegates argued that the operation was "legal" since it was aimed
at a vehicle transferring military men.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the cease-fire monitoring committee at
the end of its meeting simply said that "an exchange of views were
useful."
</P>
<P>
It reiterated the importance to "precisely comply with the
cease-fire understanding " which Israel and Lebanon reached on
April 26, 1996, barring the fighting parties in south Lebanon from
attacking civilian targets.
</P>
<P>
It was under the April understanding that the committee
comprising representatives from France, Israel, Lebanon, Syria
and the United States was set up.
</P>
<P>
Israeli artillery bombarded today vicinities of a number of
villages opposite the buffer enclave this morning, causing no
casualties.
</P>
<P>
The Jewish state established the 1,100-square-kilometer
"security zone" in 1985 ostensibly to protect northern Israel from
cross-border attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
