<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Hikes School Fees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 24 (xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe government will, with
effect from May 1, increase primary and secondary day school fees by
an average 66.5 percent for pupils in urban schools, while the
average increase for children of foreign parents is 309.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the increases today, Deputy Education Minister
William Gumbochuma said while primary school pupils in rural day
schools would continue to learn free of charge, termly fees for rural
secondary schools would go up by 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
''This is an on-going process of recovering part of the costs of
education in order to reduce the budget deficit and to improve the
quality of education by providing more and better materials and
facilities,'' said Gumbochuma. enditem



