district headquarters to the affected villages was in some areas
hampered by breakdown of road transportation. As a resualt, he said,
small amounts of food are being ferried on bicycles and head-loads for
long distances.
</P>
<P>
Mewnwhile the president said the NGO agencies that are distributing
the food supplies also need financial assistance to meet
transportation costs.
</P>
<P>
