<HEADLINE> China, Germany's Major Trading Partner in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, April 24 (Xinhua) -- China has become Germany's biggest
trading partner in the developing world, with its exports to
Germany totaling 17.9 billion marks (10.4 billion US dollars) last
year, up 12 percent from 1995, according to official data released
today.
</P>
<P>
This is compared with 95.1 billion mark (55.3 billion dollar)
worth exports to Germany by the developing world as a whole in
1996.
</P>
<P>
The Economics Ministry said in a report that last year German
exports to China increased by 1 percent to 10.9 billion marks (6.3
billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The developing countries last year accounted for 14 percent of
German exports and 14 percent of German imports, it was added.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, German exports to developing countries
last year grew by 2.2 percent to total 112.8 billion marks (65.6
billion dollars), while imports from developing countries rose 2.6
percent. 
</P>
