<HEADLINE> Chinese President Calls for Closer Sino-Russian Economic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
here today that the Sino-Russian economic and trade ties must be
improved to keep pace with the development of the political
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Talking with Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin here
this afternoon, Jiang said cooperation in the economic and trade
field between the two countries enjoys exceptional geographic
advantages and the two economies are largely complementary.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told Chernomyrdin that both he and President Boris
Yeltsin have considered it necessary to make efforts to increase
economic and trade ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"In my view, both our two countries should have farther
foresight on such an issue," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang held that the two countries are capable of launching
more large- and medium-sized long-term cooperation projects,
adding that a series of proposals have been put forward by the
Chinese side.
</P>
<P>
The proposals include setting up economic and technological
development zones in Russia, opening a China trade center in
Moscow, establishing a coordination committee of border economic
and trade cooperation and signing a framework agreement on
Sino-Russian long-term trade, Jiang said, adding that he expects
the Russian side to consider those proposals positively.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the two countries can further expand cooperation
in the fields of nuclear energy, power generation, petroleum and
natural gas, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese President expressed his hope that the two
countries' strategic coordination partnership will be deepened and
strengthened in the economic field.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said that Jiang's view on Sino-Russian economic
and trade ties is of guiding importance, to which the Russian side
attaches great importance.
</P>
<P>
At present, experts of the two countries are making feasibility
studies on some major projects and Russia is interested in taking
part in China's projects in nuclear power, petroleum, natural gas
and coal industries, Chernomyrdin said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that Russia has advanced technology in the fields of
space industry and pipeline transportation, Chernomyrdin said that
there exists great potential in economic, trade and technological
cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Describing Jiang's visit to Russia as a milestone in bilateral
relations, Chernomyrdin said that it will remarkably facilitate
bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Jiang conveyed to Chernomyrdin greetings
from Chinese Premier Li Peng and said that Li expects to meet him
again. Chernomyrdin said that he expects to achieve positive
results during his coming visit to China, which is scheduled for
June. 
</P>
