<HEADLINE> Seminar on African Medicine Ends in Yaounde </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- A two-day seminar to sensitize
Africans on their governments' medicine policies ended here today.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, delegates from seven
French-speaking African countries and France sought ways of
fighting drug peddling, discussed the policies of health
insurance and the importance of local drug production.
</P>
<P>
They decided drug manufacturers and distributors in
French-speaking Africa and France will jointly seek solutions to
health problems in the continent.
</P>
<P>
They also called upon French-speaking African countries to
foster greater partnership with French pharmaceutical industries
in order to acquire necessary technology for the local production
of essential drugs. 
</P>
