<HEADLINE> U.S. Unemployment Claims Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. Labor Department
today said that new claims for state unemployment insurance
benefits during the week ended April 19 fell to a seasonally
adjusted 324,000, a level below analyst expectations.
</P>
<P>
Initial unemployment claims decreased by 8,000 after rising by
8,000 to 332,000 in the previous week, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts had expected claims to drop by only 2,000 to
330,000. The decrease was the first in four weeks.
</P>
<P>
For the week ended April 19, the four-week moving average of
initial claims increased by 3,250 to 323,000. The last time the
average was as high as the week ended February 8, when the level
was 325,500. 
</P>
</TEXT>
