<HEADLINE>   21 Killed in Bomb Explosion in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A time bomb explosion today
killed 21 people and injured 20 others in Algeria, police sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The bomb, planted on a passenger train, went off when the train
was passing the eastern suburb of Algiers province.
</P>
<P>
Rescue teams were sent to the scene immediately after the
incident took place. No one claimed responsibility for the
explosion so far.
</P>
<P>
Algeria witnessed three terrorist attacks last week, killing
more than 100 people including women and children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
