<HEADLINE> Ice Hockey Worlds to be Expanded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The number of the teams for the
1998 World Ice Hockey Championships will be increased to 16 from
12, the International Ice Hockey Federation (IIHF) said here on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
IIHF president Rene Fasel said, "We want to open up the world
championship to other countries. The next championship will have
a team from the Far East, Japan and the host country Switzerland
will also be guaranteed a place."
</P>
<P>
The 16 teams in next year's championship will include the top
11 teams from this year's championship and host Switzerland,
Japan, B pool champions Belarus and two more teams from a
qualifying tournament.
</P>
<P>
The teams will be divided into four groups of four, the top two
in each advancing to last four.
</P>
<P>
IIHF officials said the addition of four more teams would not
add to the length of the championship which this year runs for
almost three weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
