<HEADLINE> Tech Fair to Be Held in Singapore in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Innovators, technology start-up
companies, multi-national corporations' (MNCs') technology labs
and other technology providers from more than 13 countries and
regions around the world will gather here at a "tech fair" in
September to promote technology business development in Singapore
and the region.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore National Science and Technology Board (NSTB)
announced today that a unique blend of three events positioned to
develop Singapore into a focal point for comprehensive technology
business development will be held at the fair.
</P>
<P>
The three events include TechConnet, a technology exhibition
showcasing upstream pre-product technologies; TechVenture, a
technology venture forum for financing institutions and technology
entrepreneurs; and an international conference on "Using R&AMP;D to
Create Business Growth."
</P>
<P>
"This is the first time such a major effort in the region is
designed specifically to provide opportunities for exchanges,
upstream technology trading, high-tech business ventures, and
collaborative partnerships to be made," the NSTB said.
</P>
<P>
The NSTB hopes the exhibition will allow large MNCs and smaller
companies to meet and strike deals to market and develop new
technologies.
</P>
<P>
Yau Lee Ying, the NSTB's Technology Development Division
Director, said the exhibitors will be coming from the United
States, China, Israel, Malaysia, France, Japan, and Germany and
other countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
It is time to promote technology business development as the
technology market here in the region has started to mature, she
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
