<HEADLINE> China to Set Up Global Oceanic Information Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The State Oceanic Administration
of China will spend the next several years setting up a global
oceanic information network designed to integrate China's oceanic
economy into the world market.
</P>
<P>
A high-ranking official with the administration said that the
network will be connected with international oceanic
organizations, aid organizations, and related domestic departments.
</P>
<P>
The network will consist of two data banks, one covering the
current situation of world oceanic exploration, the other
involving the domestic investment environment.
</P>
<P>
The network will be linked with oceanic institutions both in
China and throughout the world, to get the latest information on
oceanic development and market demand. It also will release
information on the international oceanic economic market and
trade. 
</P>
