<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for More Sino-Russian Cultural Exchanges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TULA, Russia, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese President
Jiang Zemin today called for the further increase of cultural
exchanges between China and Russia.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the call during a visit to the former residence, now
a museum, of the late Russian writer Lev Tolstoy, which locates in
the Tula region, about 200 kilometers south of Moscow.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president noted that while Tolstoy's works are very
popular in China, the world-renowned writer himself was also
interested in the Chinese culture and literature.
</P>
<P>
Exchanges in the cultural field between the two countries are
very important, he said.
</P>
<P>
Vasily Starodubtsev, Governor of the Tula region, presided over
a welcome ceremony featuring Russian folk arts in honor of Jiang
at the manor.
</P>
<P>
Tolstoy's great-great-grandson explained to Jiang the history
of the manor and collections in the museum.
</P>
<P>
Jiang spoke highly of Tolstoy's contribution to world
literature and said that Tolstoy's works, including "Peace and
War," "Resurrection" and others, were among his favorites.
</P>
<P>
"Tolstoy's works are treasures of not only the Russian people,
but also the Chinese people and the people all over the world,"
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
When Tolstoy's great-great-grandson said that he plans to
organize an exhibition in China to show Tolstoy's works and things
left, Jiang said that many Chinese will be glad to visit the
exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Jiang is currently on a five-day state visit to Russia, which
is to end tomorrow. 
</P>
