<HEADLINE> HK to Set Up Putonghua Training, Testing Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 25 (Xinhua) -- An agreement was signed here
today to establish a Putonghua Training and Testing Center at the
Hong Kong Institute of Education with the assistance of the
mainland Center for Training and Testing Putonghua.
</P>
<P>
The center is intended to provide services which will help
raise the standard of Putonghua in Hong Kong and facilitate the
development of benchmark standards for Putonghua subjects as part
of the institute's quality assurance mechanism.
</P>
<P>
Six members of the institute's Putonghua teaching staff will
conduct Putonghua training courses and tests in Hong Kong for
students, teachers and employees from other educational bodies in
Hong Kong according to criteria established by China's State
Language Commission.
</P>
<P>
Director C. K. Leung of the institute said the institute looks
forward to playing a significant role in contributing to the
enhancement of the standards of training and testing of Putonghua
competency in Hong Kong.  
