<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Southern African Development
Community (SADC) has been urged to take concrete steps to ensure
gender issues were considered in all its policies and programs,
reported the South African Press Association today from Mbabane,
capital of Swaziland.
</P>
<P>
The Women in Development Southern Africa Awareness Project,
currently holding a five-day workshop in Mbabane, challenged the SADC
and other regional policy-makers to include an awareness of gender in
their work, said the report.
</P>
<P>
