<HEADLINE> Traffic Accidents Increase in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A total of 5,145 traffic accidents
occurred across Vietnam in the first quarter of 1997, up 24.1
percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The accidents, on roads, inland waterways and railways, killed
1,522 people and injured 5,697 others, media reports quoted the
General Department of Police as saying today.
</P>
<P>
While accidents on roads accounted for 95 percent of the
quarterly total, leaving 1,412 dead and 5,650 injured, drivers
breaching traffic regulations were mainly to blame for the
casualties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
