<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Famous Painter Liang Huangzhou Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Liang Huangzhou, a famous
master of traditional Chinese painting, died of illness in
Guangzhou on April 23. He was 72.
</P>
<P>
Liang, who went by the name Huang Zhou, was also a member of
the Standing Committee of the Eighth National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference and curator of
the Yanhuang Art Museum.
</P>
<P>
Best known for his depictions of animals, especially donkeys,
and also pictures of Uygur people, Huang received national and
international awards for his paintings.
</P>
<P>
A native of Lixian County, Hebei Province, Liang joined the
People's Liberation Army in 1948 and worked as professional
painter and head of the art organization of the Department of
Culture of the Northwest Military Area Command.
</P>
<P>
After 1975, he served as adviser to the Arts and Crafts
Corporation of the Ministry of Light Industry; vice-president of
the Academy of Traditional Chinese Paintings; and standing council
member of Chinese Artists' Association. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
