<HEADLINE> Flower Exports to Earn Uganda 65 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Flower exports will earn Uganda 65
million US dollars by the year 2001, reported the local daily
the New Vision today.
</P>
<P>
Flower exports earned the country 15 million dollars last year
while the figure was almost zero years ago.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, the progress is due to more land set
aside by the Ugandan government for flower growing in the country
and more cold stores set up for flower reservation. For instance,
a new cold storage was set up recently in Entebbe near Kampala
with a total capacity of 50 tons for flower reservation. 
</P>
