<HEADLINE> Santoro Advanced in Monte Carlo Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Fabrice Santoro of France advanced
into the semi-finals of the Monte Carlo Open tennis tournament
with a 6-3 and 7-5 victory over Carlos Costa on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the week Santoro, who needed a wild card invitation
into the tournament, eliminated Sergi Bruguera and Thomas Muster.
The pair had won five Monte Carlo and three French Opens between
them.
</P>
<P>
The tournament has taken a beating this year with 10 of the top
16 players failing to get past the second round including Pete
Sampras, Boris Becker and Muster who lost in one afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Santoro, ranked 90th in the world, takes on his third Spanish
player in a row Saturday, Alex Corretja who routed Christian Ruud,
6-2, 6-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
