<HEADLINE> Singapore Labor Movement Tries to Secure Employment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Singapore's labor movement, the
National Trade Union Congress (NTUC), is taking it as its aim in
the 21st century to ensure that workers have lifelong employment
and not prematurely shortened work life.
</P>
<P>
In a comment in NTUC News ahead of May Day next week, the labor
movement says Singapore's workers need to keep on improving
because the country's competitors won't be standing still.
</P>
<P>
Although an international risk analysis firm, BERI, has rated
Singapore's workforce as top, the NTUC says there is definitely
room for improvement. Singapore is not rated first in workers'
attitude and technical skills, it noted.
</P>
<P>
Singapore will also have to contend with competition from
developing economies like the neighboring countries which have the
benefit of a larger population and lower wages and land costs, it
said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the workers in Singapore will have to train and
retrain so as to stay ahead of competition, it stressed.  
</P>
