<TEXT>
<P>
Colombo, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A new development project for
improving and protecting the environment of urban areas in Sri
Lanka started today under the Environmental Village Program of the
Ministry of Environment.
</P>
<P>
The project was inaugurated by Minister Srimani Athulathmudali
in Walawwattha and Kothelawelapura of Ratmalana, about 15
kilometers from Colombo, this morning.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of this kind of environmental development
project is to protect the environment of the urban dwellers in the
vicinity.
</P>
<P>
The sources said they have paid special attention to sanitary
facilities in the urban areas.
</P>
<P>
"The main problem faced by the urban dwellers is the lack of
sanitary facilities. Due to this they are at risk of getting
various diseases," they said.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, we introduced this program as an awareness program
for the urban dwellers and under this project they can clean up
their areas," the sources explained.
</P>
<P>
Apart from this, the ministry hopes to give a new look to the
houses, roads and drainage and make people plant trees to protect
the environment, the sources added.  
</P>
