<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA General Staff Chief Meets Philippine Visitor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of the General
Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), said today he
hoped to maintain the momentum for the relations between the
Chinese and Philippines armed forces and further enhance mutual
trust, understanding, and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Fu, who is also a member of China's Central Military
Commission, made the remark here this afternoon when meeting with
Fernando Campos, undersecretary of defense of the Philippines,
noting that in the past few years, relations between the two armed
forces have made a rapid progress with joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and the Philippines are two friendly
neighbors, and bilateral relations have witnessed a smooth
development in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the development of bilateral friendship and
cooperation is not only in the fundamental interest of the two
peoples, but also conducive to peace and stability in the
Asia-Pacific region and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
He said that China, which is concentrating on economic
construction, needs a peaceful international environment,
especially a peaceful and stable surrounding environment.
</P>
<P>
Fu also briefed Campos on China's military building.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his thanks for having the opportunity to visit
China, Campos said he hoped that the friendship and cooperation
between the two countries and the two armed forces will become
even closer.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
