<DOCNO> XIE19970425.0150 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Charity Foundation Set Up in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong and Shanghai Bank
has donated some 25 million HK dollars here today to set up a new
charity foundation in the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract signed here today, the Hong
Kong Bank Foundation will offer the China Charity Federation (CCF)
10 percent of the interest (equalling 2.5 million HK dollars)
obtained from its donation every year to support the charity
programs, especially non-profit agencies, in the inland areas.
</P>
<P>
HKSB will also help the CCF's scheme of supporting the elderly
and orphans, and providing aid to those in distress and poverty
with the fund.
</P>
<P>
The bank expressed the hope to draw some 500,000 yuan (60,000
US dollars) from the first year's interest and donate it to the
CCF, while making the application to be a founder of the CCF.
</P>
<P>
The CCF accepted the bank as a founder and permanent executive.
</P>
<P>
The China Charity Federation is a non-governmental charity
organization approved by the Chinese government. It currently has
59 institutionals members in the country.
</P>
<P>
Attending today donation ceremony were Tian Jiyun,
vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress, Ma Wenrui, former vice-chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, and officials from other departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
