<HEADLINE> French Grand Prix Gets Green Light </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- A dispute over television rights,
which might lead to the cancellation of this season's French Grand
Prix, has been settled, the International Automobile Federation
(FIA) said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The difficulties surrounding access to the French Grand Prix
by unauthorised television crews have been resolved and the event
is now confirmed as a round in the 1997 Formula One World
Championship," said a FIA spokesman. 
</P>
