<HEADLINE> Chinese, Beninian Supreme Court Presidents Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Vice-President of the Supreme
People's Court of China Gao Changli met with a delegation from the
Beninian Supreme Court led by its President Abraham Zinzindohoue
here today.
</P>
<P>
Gao met with the Beninian guests on behalf of the President of
the Supreme People's Court Ren Jianxin.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in the Diaoyutai State Guest House, the
two sides exchanged views on the legal systems and law enforcement
in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Gao briefed the visitors on China's reform, opening up, and
modernization drive. He said that Zinzindohoue's China trip will
greatly enhance the friendly relations between the two courts and
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Zinzindohoue is on his first trip to China at the invitation of
Ren Jianxin.
</P>
<P>
Zinzindohoue said that Benin is willing to expand its links
with China in all fields including the legal system. 
</P>
