<HEADLINE> Share Prices Remain Low on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Share prices finished mixed in
dull trading on the Singapore market while the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index fell by 0.57 points to close at 2019.6
today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 93.91 million units, valued
at 302.03 million Singapore dollars (about 209.74 million U.S.
dollars). Advances outnumbered declines by 157 to 129 while 334
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Singapore Telecom was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 6.51 million units. It was followed by
Ber Group which had 2.79 million shares traded. The Hong Kong Land
was next with 2.45 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Samanda Holdings topped the gainers' list as it rose by 60
cents to finish at 9.1 dollars. The Singapore Airlines (SIA)
Foreign gained 40 cents to end at 12.7 Singapore dollars while
BerLei closed 28 cents higher at 2 dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, TAC 200 was the biggest loser of the day as it
declined by 52 cents to end at 4.98 U.S. dollars. Asean Fund and
the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign fell by 30 cents each
to close at 16.1 U.S. dollars and 26.8 Singapore dollars
respectively. JMH 400 was 25 cents lower at 5.4 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
