<HEADLINE> Nigerian Army to Test Combat Readiness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The Army of Nigeria will begin
special manoeuvres to test the combat readiness of troops on
Monday in its major training area in Kontagora, Niger State.
</P>
<P>
Army spokesman Felix Chukwuma said on Thursday that the
exercise, code-named "Eagle Ring", would involve other arms of
the military, particularly the Air Force.
</P>
<P>
The exercise will focus on the Army's potency in terms of
individual and group training support, troop motivation and
conflict leadership at all levels and general administration
under extreme war situations.
</P>
<P>
"To a large extent, the exercise will showcase infantry skills
and manouevres in all phases of war though the amour, artillery,
engineers, medicals and other support arms and services will play
crucial roles for the attainment of its objectives," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
