<DOCNO> XIE19970425.0161 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Envoy, Mbeki Meet over Zairean Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 25 (Xinhua) -- South African Deputy
President Thabo Mbeki held discussions with U.N. special envoy
Mohamed Sahnoun in Pretoria Thursday on the proposed Zairean
peace talks, an informed source said here today.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki and Sahnoun focused on the timing and venue of
face-to-face talks between Zairean President Mobutu Sese Seko and
rebel leader Laurent Kabila, the source said.
</P>
<P>
Sahnoun, who arrived in South Africa on Thursday from Namibia,
declined to give details about the talks. However, he told
reporters that negotiators from the Zairean warring sides were
"still working" on the venue of peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Sahnoun is due to meet South African Deputy Foreign Minister
Aziz Pahad today for more talks on the same issue, the source
said.
</P>
<P>
Pahad told parliament Thursday that Mobutu was still committed
to the meeting with Kabila, but suggested that a time and venue
should be reconsidered.
</P>
<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela has offered to host the
talks in his country, but Mobutu reportedly wants a venue closer
to Zaire, as he is suffering from cancer and feels unable to
travel long distances. 
</P>
