<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Sees Rises in Ocean Vessels, Seaborne Cargo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 24 (Xinhua) -- In the fourth quarter of 1996,
10,788 ocean vessels with a total capacity of 47.3 million net
registered tons (NRTs) entered Hong Kong, official figures showed
today.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same period in 1995, the number of vessels
grew by 1 percent and the capacity by 6 percent, according to
figures released by the Hong Kong Census and Statistics
Department.
</P>
<P>
NRT is a unit measure in volume terms of the space of a vessel
available for carrying passengers or goods. One NRT is equivalent
to 100 cubic feet (2.83 cubic meters).
</P>
<P>
During the same period, there were 10,829 outgoing ocean
vessels with a total capacity of 47.2 million NRTs. Compared with
a year earlier, there was little change in the number of vessels
but an increase of 5 percent in capacity.
</P>
<P>
The total tonnage of seaborne inward cargo, comprising imports
and inward transshipment, was estimated at 23.2 million tons in
the quarter, up 4 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, seaborne outward cargo, comprising domestic
exports, re-exports and outward transshipment, gained 3 percent to
reach 10.5 million tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
