1.2 billion HK dollars (154.8 million U.S. dollars) in its initial
public offering of shares late next month.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Enterprise is a mini conglomerate with diversified
businesses including manufacturing, retailing, road operation,
telecommunications and property investments.
</P>
<P>
According to officials of the Hong Kong Stock Exchange, the
exchange has received 19 listing applications with 10 approved by
the exchange's listing committee including Zhejiang Express and
Beijing Enterprise. 
