<DOCNO> XIE19970425.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen to Have More Promising Ties with Hong Kong: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen City, China's special
economic zone that borders Hong Kong, will see closer economic
ties with Hong Kong after the latter's return to the motherland, a
senior official of Shenzhen has said.
</P>
<P>
Li Youwei, secretary of the Shenzhen City Communist Party
Committee, said that after Hong Kong's return, the "one country,
two systems" principle shall not be confused, but the two places
will have better economic ties.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks Thursday when interviewed by reporters from
some 30 news institutions of foreign countries, such as Japan,
Britain, the United States, Finland, Germany, Italy, and Canada.
</P>
<P>
After Hong Kong's return, Shenzhen and Hong Kong will have
closer relations, Li said, explaining that the historic event will
bring about more opportunity for Shenzhen's opening wider to the
outside world, and the tendency of economic symbiosis will grow
more obvious.
</P>
<P>
To meet the demand for more freight and personnel exchanges,
Shenzhen City is preparing for new passages leading to Hong Kong,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Li Youwei also mentioned that the two sides will enhance
cooperation in high-tech industry, as well as in the information,
financial, trade, and tourism fields.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
