<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African Round Table Moves Headquarters to S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The African Business Round
Table (ABR), whose aim is to promote African private initiatives,
has relocated its headquarters to Johannesburg, South Africa from
Abidjan, economic capital of Cote d'Ivoire, said a source here
today.
</P>
<P>
The ABR said on Thursday in a statement that the relocation
was a sign of recognising South Africa's leading role in African
development.
</P>
<P>
The ABR was established in 1990 by the African Development
Bank to promote the private sector on the continent.
</P>
<P>
The ABR is an political, independent and non-profit making
business organisation whose membership included successful
entrepreneurs in all sectors across Africa and abroad, said the
source.
</P>
<P>
ABR executive secretary Karamo Sonko said the ABR had
relocated its headquarters to South Africa after realising the
country could become the locomotive of economic development in
Africa. 
</P>
