<HEADLINE> Making Iceland's Health Care Products Available in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Health care products from Iceland
will soon be available on the Chinese market, with the signing of
a long-term cooperation agreement between Iceland's Lysi Company
and China's Peace Company, today.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Peace Century Economic and Trading Co. Ltd. will
serve as the exclusive marketing agent for the Icelandic company in
China.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is the first cooperation between China and
Iceland in health care products. Public health officials of both
countries attended the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Contacts between China and Iceland have been growing since the
two established official ties in 1971. High-level exchanges have
increased cooperation between the two countries in politics, the
economy, culture, and trade.
</P>
<P>
Iceland abounds in marine products. Lysi's Omega-III fish oil,
which is believed to be effective in improving memory and slowing
down aging, sells well on the world market.
</P>
<P>
China Peace Company is a large state-owned enterprise run by
the Soong Ching Ling Foundation of China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
