<HEADLINE> China To Compile "Chinese Stamp History" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Philatelists have begun
compiling the first volume of "Chinese Stamp History," which will
deal with Chinese customs postal services during the 1878-1896
period.
</P>
<P>
The book will have nine volumes. The first volume will be
compiled by philatelists from Tianjin and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
China will hold a world stamps exhibition for the first time in
1999, and the 22nd Congress of Universal Postal Union will be held
in Beijing the same year. "Chinese Stamp History" will be a gift
to the congress, and will be presented at the documentary works
section of the "99 World Stamps Exhibition".
</P>
<P>
Philatelists agreed that compiling the book is conducive to
rescuing rare historical material and advancing the international
postal cultural exchanges. 
</P>
