<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi PM to Hold Talks with Business Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dhaka, April 25 (Xinhua)--- Bangladesh Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina will meet with leaders of the business community on May 3
to discuss the latest economic situation in the country, said
sources in the Federation of Bangladesh Chambers of Commerce and
Industry (FBCCI).
</P>
<P>
The FBCCI is arranging the meeting which would be attended by
prominent business leaders representing different chambers and
trade associations, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The meeting might be largely attended and the prime minister
would prefer to hear to the business community's views on
important issues pertaining to both business and politics,
according to Samson Chowdhury, president of the Metropolitan
Chamber of Commerce and Industry (MCCI).
</P>
<P>
He said the list of priority items for discussion should
include virtually everything affecting the economy, including law
and order, investment, capital market and the fiscal and monetary
policies.
</P>
<P>
He complained that the government borrowings from the banking
system were creating problems for the private sector borrowers
from commercial banks and it would have adverse impact on public
resource management and on the growth of the private sector.
</P>
<P>
Amjad Khan Chowdhury, a former vice president of the MCCI and
one of the country's leading entrepreneurs, said he felt it was
appropriate time for the prime minister to take stock of the
situation.
</P>
<P>
He said the business leaders should take this opportunity to
give the prime minister first-hand account of the bureaucratic
impediments they were facing and its negative impact on the
private sector's growth. 
</P>
