Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) to admit Romania to the
alliance in the first batch of new members.
</P>
<P>
The appeal, which was passed by a joint parliamentary meeting
today, says NATO membership is a top priority of Romanian foreign
policy.
</P>
<P>
It said Romania was qualified because it was a democracy, had a
stable political situation and an important geographical and
strategic position.
</P>
<P>
Romania had the ability to meet the spending of joining NATO.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Foreign Minister Adrian Severin, now visiting the
United States, urged Washington to back Romania for the first NATO
batch in July, 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
