<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Opposition Urged to Join By-Polls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dhaka, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina Thursday called upon the opposition Bangladesh Nationalist
Party (BNP) to take part in by-elections to help strengthen the
electoral process, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
"I call upon the opposition to join the elections, instead of
boycotting those," she told a coordination meeting in Gopalganj
City, about 100 kilometers southwest of the capital Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
The main opposition BNP has been boycotting all by-elections
since the defeat of its candidates in the Laksmipur and
Mirersharai constituencies vacated by its chairperson Begum
Khaleda Zia.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said her government was taking all steps to
ensure transparency and accountability of the electoral system
and, to that end, giving training to the election officials.
</P>
<P>
For the neutrality of election, neither she nor any minister of
her government went to any constituency as per the request of the
Election Commission, Sheikh Hasina added.
</P>
<P>
Reacting to the call made by the prime minister, BNP Secretary
General Abdul Mannan said Thursday night that there is no
possibility of holding a fair election under the present partisan
chief election commissioner, Abu Hena.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to join the forthcoming by-election in the
Manikganj-3 constituency, provided the chief election commissioner
resigns," said the opposition leader.  
</P>
