<HEADLINE> Dhaka Stock Exchange Passes Negative Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Stocks slumped with low turnover on
the Dhaka Stock Exchange (DSE) Thursday, ending yet another
negative week in a shaky and volatile market.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark DSE all share price index fell 31.86 points, or
3.02 percent, closing at 1022.20, the lowest in recent times.
</P>
<P>
During the last trading week from last Saturday to Thursday,
the DSE price index rose on two days and fell on three days,
overall shedding 90.89 points or 9.57 percent, opening at 1113.00
and closing at 1022.20.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the market capitalization decreased to 85.08 billion
taka (about 2.13 billion U.S. dollars), which was 7.64 billion
taka (about 191 million dollars) lower than the balance of the
previous week.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the week's lackluster trade was marked by
retail sales pressure matched by retail limit buy orders with
price dictated by the buyers.
</P>
<P>
There were no bulk sales offers or bulk buy orders, they added.
</P>
<P>
On the last trading day Thursday, 86 issues declined in value,
24 advanced and three remained unchanged out of the 113 traded.
</P>
<P>
A DSE official said that the market lacking confidence was
hungry for some good news. "It is high time to take care by all in
the society including the authorities to rebuild the badly needed
confidence to put the market on a recovery path," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
