<HEADLINE> Russian Duma Calls for Protest against NATO Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Russian State Duma (the lower
house of parliament) today urged all Russian authorities, parties
and organizations to protest on May 9 against expansion of the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
May 9 is the holiday for "Victory in the Anti-Fascist War."
</P>
<P>
The State Duma made the appeal following a vote, 253 for and 14
against. The appeal was drafted by the Anti-NATO Commission of the
lower house.
</P>
<P>
The appeal said the Russian people should not ignore the
increasing external threat to their country when they celebrated
"Victory Day."
</P>
<P>
The alliance's eastward expansion would put Russia under "the
most serious military threat" in the recent 50 years, the appeal
said.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, the State Duma also issued a statement, urging
parliaments of NATO member states to "understand" Russia's concern
about NATO's eastward expansion, and take necessary measures to
avoid new confrontation in Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
