<HEADLINE> C.American Nations Agree on Integration of Agencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Foreign ministers of the
Central American countries have agreed to merge their institutions
involved in integration.
</P>
<P>
The agreement came after the Central American foreign and
economics ministers met Wednesday in Guatemala City.
</P>
<P>
Guatemalan Foreign Minister Eduardo Stein said that more
than 15 entities responsible for the integration in economic,
commercial, political, social and environmental fields were at
present autonimous.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the institutional merging was to facilitate
regional coordination, cut costs and to speed up the process in
line with other trade blocs, Stein said.
</P>
<P>
The ministers responsible for regional integration agreed to
continue the analysis of the reorganization on May 9, in Costa
Rica -- one day after the summit of the isthmus presidents with
United States President Bill Clinton.
</P>
<P>
The merging will also be on the agenda of the coming Central
American summit, which is to be held in Panama in mid-June.
</P>
