<DOCNO> XIE19970425.0256 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slovakia to Restrict Imports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Slovak government will take
measures to restrict imports from May 1, Minister of Finance
Sergej Kozlik told the press Wednesday in Bratislava, capital of
Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
Under the measures, the importers are required to hand in 20
percent of the total imports in cash as guarantees, otherwise the
imported goods cannot clear the customs.
</P>
<P>
Import of non-alcoholic beverages will be restricted to 45
million liters per year; if necessary, import quotas will be
imposed on agricultural and industrial products.
</P>
<P>
These tentative actions were taken to reduce spiraling foreign
trade deficits in the country and it is noticed that they came
immediately after the Czech Republic announced measures to
restrict imports and encourage exports to reduce its own huge
trade deficits.
</P>
<P>
Kozlik said in restricting imports Slovakia is not retaliating
against Czechs, but is trying to reduce the adverse effect on the
Slovak economy inflicted by the czech measures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
