<HEADLINE> Fair Lures Worldwide Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 25 (Xinhua) -- The first national fair for
investment and trade will make its debut in Xiamen on September
8-13, "China Daily" reports today.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing based newspaper quotes Sun Zhenyu, vice-minister of
Foreign Trade and Economic Co-operation as saying that the
national fair is aimed at promoting and guiding investment
activities, while focusing on the quality of foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 key projects for foreign investment and a
variety of commodities will be recommended to foreign business
persons by nearly 40 domestic groups participating in the fair.
</P>
<P>
The fair, dubbed China Fair for International Investment and
Trade (CFIIT), evolved from the annual Fujian Fair for Investment
and Trade, which has been held successfully since 1987.
</P>
<P>
The fair will help accelerate the development of trade and
economic co-operation between foreign countries and China's
central and western parts, as well as trade between foreign-funded
ventures in the country's coastal areas and those in relatively
under-developed areas. Positioned on the brink of the Taiwan
Straits, the fair will be conducive to economic and trade
co-operation between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
More than 2,000 Taiwan business people have expressed their
intention to participate in CFIIT and also the Cross-Strait
Commodity Fair, which coincides with CFIIT.
</P>
<P>
China has been the world's second largest recipient of foreign
investment for three consecutive years, Vice-Minister Sun Zhenyu
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
