<HEADLINE> Olympiakos Win European Club Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Olympiakos of Greece took the title
fo the European club basketball title after beating Barcelona
73-58 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It was Olympiakos' third final in four years but their first
title. They lost in 1994 and 1995 in the finals.
</P>
<P>
The Greek team, inspired as they had been in Tuesday's
semi-finals against Ljubljana by playmaker David Rivers, had a
slow start but fought back strongly to win the match.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona led early in the first half, but Olympiakos took the
lead 31-29 at halftime as Rivers contributed 14 points alone.
</P>
<P>
Olympiakos scored eight points in a row while Barcelona failed
to score in the first four minutes.
</P>
<P>
Rivers led the scoring 26. He scored 28 points in the
semi-finals. 
</P>
