<HEADLINE> China's ICBC Bank Launchs Representative Office in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FRANKFURT, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) today opened a representative office in
Germany's banking center Frankfurt.
</P>
<P>
With assets worth 3,500 billion RMB (about 422 billion U.S.
dollars) at the end of 1996, and a net of about 30,000 branches
across China, the ICBC is one of the biggest state-own commercial
banks of China which has a market share of 26 percent and 27
percent in domestic deposit and credit business respectively.
</P>
<P>
With its business mainly focusing on the domestic markets, the
ICBC has started to put more emphasis on overseas expansion in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
The Frankfurt representative office is the eighth ICBC
subsidary units established outside China and the second
representative office in Europe after the one in London. 
</P>
