<HEADLINE> U.S. Welcomes Russia-China Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 24 (Xinhua) -- The United States welcomed a
treaty signed by China, Russia and three other Central Asian
countries over the reduction of their troops along a 4,300- mile
border, the State Department said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The United States welcomes the agreement signed between Russia
and China because we hope that Russia and China will fully
normalize their bilateral relationship and take efforts to make
sure that the long border between the two countries is stable and
peaceful," spokesman Burns said at a regular briefing.
