<HEADLINE> Little Changes in New York Stocks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 24 (Xinhua) -- Thursday's New York stocks
almost got the same results as the previous session after
retreating from an early rally led by the technology sector, which
had risen at an encouraging earnings report from IBM.
</P>
<P>
Just before the close on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial
average fell 20.47 points to 6,792.25.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 10-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 485.42 million
shares as against 489.25 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Technology shares and smaller-company issues outperformed the
blue-chip sector.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list fell 2.46 to 771.18, and
the NYSE's composite index fell 1.09 to 403.62.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 0.96 to 1,228.10, and the
American Stock Exchange composite index rose 0.59 to 543.95.
</P>
<P>
For the second straight day, stocks were pressured by the bond
market, where interest rates rose again amid worries that new
economic reports might heighten investors' recent inflation
worries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
